						<summary>

						<p>Two pices broken slab lying to the north of the tank.</p>						

						<p>Rājēndra-Chola (I) [1016-17 A.D.]</p>						

						<p>This record refers itself to the fourth year of the reign of <hi rend="bold">Kō-Parakēsarivarman Rājēndra-chōḻa</hi> and states that the tank was dug by Dōramma Uttavaseṭṭi son of Narisānti-seṭṭi and Sōmaya son of Paramaṇḍala Gavaṟe-seṭṭi. The record, in characters of about the 10th11th century A.D. may be assigned to <hi rend="bold">Rājēndra-chōḷa</hi> I in which case the year may correspond to 1016-17 A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
